{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The input includes a question along with relevant PubMed abstracts.",
    "For the summarization task, we use the ideal answer as the reference summary.",
    "Here, we explore two variants of a source document -(i) Snippets (BioASQ-S): the question followed by the list of relevant snippets from a collection of PubMed Abstracts, in line with the MEDVOC paper (Balde et al., 2024b), and (ii) BioASQ-Main Abstract (BioASQ-M): the question followed by the complete Pubmed abstracts.",
    "We evaluate the model-generated summaries using Rouge-L (R-L) to measure informativeness and coherence, and Concept-Score (CSr) to measure faithfulness (Zhang et al., 2023).",
    "Concept-Score measures the overlap of UMLS medical concepts (computed using QuickUMLS tool (Soldaini and Goharian, 2016)) between the generated and reference summaries."
  ],
